Package ptolemy.vergil.actor.lib

Class ShowTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • ptolemy.kernel.util.NamedObj
      • ptolemy.kernel.util.Attribute
        • ptolemy.actor.AbstractInitializableAttribute
          • ptolemy.vergil.actor.lib.ShowTypes
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, ExecutionListener, Initializable, Changeable, Debuggable, DebugListener, Derivable, HierarchyListener, ModelErrorHandler, MoMLExportable, Moveable, Nameable
    public class ShowTypes
extends AbstractInitializableAttribute
implements ExecutionListener
    This attribute, when inserted into a model causes types to be displayed on all ports at the same level of the hierarchy as this attribute. Note that this conflicts with other attributes that display info on ports, such as MonitorReceiverAttribute. The two should not be used together.
